description.p:
Fig. 8 is a flow diagram illustrating process steps of a driving method 200 according to embodiments of the present disclosure. The drive method 200 can be implemented in the driving device 100 as shown in Fig. 1. The drive method 200 comprises the steps of:
step 210: receiving a control signal and a power signal, generating a driving pulse signal based on the control signal, and generating a power pulse signal based on the power signal by a driving primary circuit;
step 220: transmitting the driving pulse signal through a second isolating transforming unit and transmitting the power pulse signal through a first isolating transforming unit to at least one driving secondary circuit by the driving primary circuit;
step 230: receiving and generating the driving signal based on the driving pulse signal by at least one driving secondary circuit so as to drive a power semiconductor switch unit;
step 240: transmitting a protection pulse signal to the driving primary circuit through an isolating transforming circuit by at least one driving secondary circuit;
step 250: receiving and generating a protection signal based on the protection pulse signal, and generating a driving terminal turn-off signal based on the protection signal by the driving primary circuit; and
step 260: outputting a driving terminal turn-off signal to turn off the power semiconductor switch unit by the driving primary circuit.

claim.claim-text:
A driving device, comprising:
a driving primary circuit (120) configured to receive a control signal and a power signal, wherein the driving primary circuit (120) is configured to generate a driving pulse signal based on the control signal, and generate a power pulse signal based on the power signal;
an isolating transforming circuit (130) configured to be coupled to the driving primary circuit (120), wherein the isolating transforming circuit (130) comprises a first isolating transforming unit (132) and a second isolating transforming unit (134), wherein the first isolating transforming unit (132) comprises one of a plurality of first pulse transformers, a second pulse transformer, and a plurality of third pulse transformers, and the second isolating transforming unit (134) comprises one of a plurality of fourth pulse transformers, a fifth pulse transformer, and a plurality of sixth pulse transformers;
wherein one of the first pulse transformers comprises a primary winding and a secondary winding, and the primary winding is electrically coupled to the driving primary circuit (120), wherein the primary windings are sequentially connected to each other in series;
wherein the second pulse transformer comprises a primary winding and a plurality of secondary windings, and the primary winding is electrically coupled to the driving primary circuit (120);
wherein one of the third pulse transformers comprises a primary winding and a secondary winding, another one of the third pulse transformers comprises a primary winding and a plurality of secondary windings, and the primary windings are electrically coupled to the driving primary circuit (120), wherein the primary windings are sequentially connected to each other in series;
wherein one of the fourth pulse transformers comprises a primary winding and a secondary winding, and the primary windings are electrically coupled to the driving primary circuit (120), wherein the primary windings are sequentially connected to each other in series;
wherein the fifth pulse transformer comprises a primary winding and a plurality of secondary windings, and the primary winding is electrically coupled to the driving primary circuit (120);
wherein one of the sixth pulse transformers comprises a primary winding and a secondary winding, another one of the sixth pulse transformers comprises a primary winding and a plurality of secondary windings, and the primary windings are electrically coupled to the driving primary circuit (120), wherein the primary windings are sequentially connected to each other in series; and
at least one driving secondary circuit (1401) configured to be coupled to the secondary windings, wherein the driving primary circuit (120) transmits the driving pulse signal through the second isolating transforming unit (134) and transmits the power pulse signal through the first isolating transforming unit (132) to the at least one driving secondary circuit (1401), wherein the at least one driving secondary circuit (1401) receives the driving pulse signal and generates a driving signal based on the driving pulse signal for driving a power semiconductor switch unit (150).

The driving device of claim 2, wherein the driving signal generating unit (124) comprises:
a driving signal receiver (124A) configured to receive the control signal;
a noise filter (124B) configured to be coupled to the driving signal receiver (124A), and configured to receive and filter the noise of the control signal; and
a first pulse modulator (124C) configured to be coupled to the noise filter (124B), wherein the first pulse modulator (124C) is configured to receive the control signal, and the first pulse modulator (124C) is configured to modulate and generate the driving pulse signal based on the control signal;
wherein the driving signal receiving unit (144) comprises:
a common-mode noise suppressor (144A) configured to be coupled to the second isolating transforming unit (134), and configured to receive and suppress the common-mode noise of the driving pulse signal;
a second pulse modulator (144B) configured to be coupled to the common-mode noise suppressor (144A), wherein the second pulse modulator (144B) is configured to receive the driving pulse signal, and the second pulse modulator (144B) is configured to demodulate and generate the driving signal based on the driving pulse signal; and
a driving power amplifier (144C) configured to be coupled to the second pulse modulator (144B), and configured to amplify the driving signal.

The driving device of claim 3, wherein the driving primary circuit (120) further comprises:
a protection signal receiving unit (126) configured to be coupled to the driving primary power circuit (122), wherein the protection signal receiving unit (126) is configured to receive a protection pulse signal and generate a protection signal based on the protection pulse signal, wherein the driving primary power circuit (122) is configured to provide the driving primary power for the protection signal receiving unit (126);
wherein the isolating transforming circuit (130) further comprises:
a third isolating transforming unit (136) configured to be coupled to the protection signal receiving unit (126);
wherein the number of the at least one driving secondary circuit (1401) is plural, and each of the driving secondary circuits (1401∼140N) further comprises:
a protection signal generating unit (146) configured to be coupled to the third isolating transforming unit (136) and the driving secondary power circuit (142), wherein each of the protection signal generating units (146) of the driving secondary circuits (1401∼140N) is configured to receive a malfunction signal, and generate a malfunction pulse signal based on the malfunction signal, wherein the third isolating transforming unit (136) is configured to receive the malfunction pulse signals and output the protection pulse signal to the protection signal receiving unit (126);
wherein the protection signal receiving unit (126) comprises:
a protection pulse receiver (126C) configured to be coupled to the third isolating transforming unit (136) and the first pulse modulator (124C), wherein the protection pulse receiver (126C) is configured to receive the protection pulse signal, and generate the protection signal based on the protection pulse signal, wherein the protection pulse receiver (126C) is configured to transmit the protection signal to the first pulse modulator (124C), and if the first pulse modulator (124C) receives the protection signal, the first pulse modulator (124C) outputs a driving terminal turn-off signal so as to turn off the power semiconductor switch unit (150); and
a protection signal transmitter (126A) configured to be coupled to the protection pulse receiver (126C), and configured to receive and transmit the protection signal.

The driving device of claim 4, wherein the protection signal generating unit (146) comprises:
a malfunction detector configured to perform detection with respect to the power semiconductor switch unit (150), the driving secondary power circuit (142), or an assembly thereof, wherein the malfunction detector generates the malfunction signal if the power semiconductor switch unit (150), the driving secondary power circuit (142), or the assembly thereof is malfunctioning;
a protection signal generator (146A) configured to be coupled to the malfunction detector, wherein the protection signal generator (146A) is configured to generate the malfunction pulse signal if the protection signal generator (146A) receives the malfunction signal; and
a logic OR gate (146B), wherein an output terminal of the logic OR gate (146B) is configured to be coupled to the protection signal generator (146A);
wherein the malfunction detector comprises:
an under-voltage malfunction detecting module (146C) configured to be coupled to a first input terminal of the logic OR gate (146B);
a short circuit malfunction detecting module (146D) configured to be coupled to a second input terminal of the logic OR gate (146B);
an over-voltage malfunction detecting module (146E) configured to be coupled to a third input terminal of the logic OR gate (146B); and
an over-heat malfunction detecting module (146F) configured to be coupled to a fourth input terminal of the logic OR gate (146B).

The driving device of claim 4, wherein the third isolating transforming unit (136) comprises a plurality of pulse transformers, and each of the pulse transformers comprises an input winding, a magnetic core, and an output winding, wherein the input winding of each of the pulse transformers is electrically coupled to one of the protection signal generating units (146) correspondingly, wherein the output windings of the pulse transformers are sequentially connected to each other in series, and electrically coupled to the protection signal receiving unit (126);

or wherein the third isolating transforming unit (136) comprises a pulse transformer, and the pulse transformer comprises a plurality of input windings, a magnetic core, and an output winding, wherein each of the input windings is electrically coupled to one of the protection signal generating units (146) correspondingly, and the output winding is electrically coupled to the protection signal receiving unit (126);

or wherein the third isolating transforming unit (136) comprises a plurality of pulse transformers, wherein one of the pulse transformers comprises an input winding, a magnetic core, and an output winding, and another one of the pulse transformers comprises a plurality of input windings, a magnetic core, and an output winding, wherein each of the input windings is electrically coupled to one of the protection signal generating units (146) correspondingly, wherein the output windings are sequentially connected to each other in series, and electrically coupled to the protection signal receiving unit (126).

