A driving method applied in a driving device (100), wherein the driving device (100) comprises a driving primary circuit (120), the isolating transforming circuit (130) of claim 1, and at least one driving secondary circuit (1401), wherein the at least one driving secondary circuit (1401) is coupled to a plurality of secondary windings of the isolating transforming circuit (130), wherein the driving method comprises:
receiving a control signal and a power signal by the driving primary circuit (120);
generating a driving pulse signal based on the control signal by the driving primary circuit (120), and generating a power pulse signal based on the power signal by the driving primary circuit (120);
transmitting the driving pulse signal through the second isolating transforming unit (134) and transmitting the power pulse signal through the first isolating transforming unit (132) to the at least one driving secondary circuit (1401); and
receiving the driving pulse signal and generating a driving signal based on the driving pulse signal by the at least one driving secondary circuit (1401) so as to drive a power semiconductor switch unit (150).

The driving method of claim 14, further comprising:
transmitting a protection pulse signal to the driving primary circuit (120) through the isolating transforming circuit (130) by the at least one driving secondary circuit (1401);
receiving the protection pulse signal and generating a protection signal based on the protection pulse signal by the driving primary circuit (120), generating a driving terminal turn-off signal based on the protection signal by the driving primary circuit (120), and generating a control terminal turn-off signal based on the protection signal by a control circuit(110); and
outputting the driving terminal turn-off signal and the control terminal turn-off signal so as to turn off the power semiconductor switch unit (150) by the driving primary circuit (120) and by the control circuit (110);
wherein the number of the power semiconductor switch unit(150) is plural, wherein the control circuit turns off the power semiconductor switch units(1501∼150N) based on the protection signal;
wherein the step of transmitting the protection pulse signal to the driving primary circuit (120) through the isolating transforming circuit (130) by the at least one driving secondary circuit (1401) comprises:
detecting the power semiconductor switch unit (150), the driving secondary circuit (1401), or an assembly thereof, and generating a malfunction signal if the power semiconductor switch unit (150), the driving secondary circuit (1401), or the assembly thereof is malfunctioning;
generating the malfunction pulse signal if the malfunction signal is received; and
generating the protection pulse signal based on the malfunction pulse signal.
